<subSubSection id="C30CE68AFF9CFF5CFF4A8C9DE403FC4C" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FF9CFF5CFF4A8C9DE403FC4C" blockId="77.[151,1437,259,1222]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF9CFF5CFF4A8C9DE613FC68" bold="true" box="[199,345,943,969]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Distribution</emphasis>
. Northwest Atlantic (
<collectingCountry id="F301F591FF9CFF5CFDDD8C9DE58AFC6B" box="[592,704,943,970]" name="Barbados" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Barbados</collectingCountry>
), Gulf of Mexico (SW Florida), Caribbean Sea (
<collectingCountry id="F301F591FF9CFF5CFB658C9DE27EFC68" box="[1256,1332,943,969]" name="Belize" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Belize</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F301F591FF9CFF5CFACD8C82E7F1FC4F" name="Venezuela" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F301F591FF9CFF5CFF428CE6E658FC4F" box="[207,274,980,1006]" name="Japan" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Japan</collectingCountry>
, Indian Ocean (
<collectingCountry id="F301F591FF9CFF5CFE4C8CE1E506FC4C" box="[449,588,979,1005]" name="Madagascar" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F301F591FF9CFF5CFDDA8CE1E583FC4F" box="[599,713,979,1006]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F301F591FF9CFF5CFD568CE1E40FFC4C" box="[731,837,979,1005]" name="Australia" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Australia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30CE68AFF9CFF5CFF4A8CC5E555FB64" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FF9CFF5CFF4A8CC5E555FB64" blockId="77.[151,1437,259,1222]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF9CFF5CFF4A8CC5E67EFBB0" bold="true" box="[199,308,1015,1041]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Remarks</emphasis>
. In addition to 5 previously described species here transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FF9CFF5CFB9E8CCAE337FBB0" authority="Just, 2022" authorityName="Just" authorityYear="2022" box="[1043,1149,1016,1041]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Minitiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF9CFF5CFB9E8CCAE337FBB0" box="[1043,1149,1016,1041]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Minitiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9626913FF9CFF5CFB088CC5E3A4FBB0" bold="true" box="[1157,1262,1015,1041]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A251D468FF9CFF5CFB088CC5E3A4FBB0" box="[1157,1262,1015,1041]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, specimens belonging to this shallow water genus have been collected in numerous places in 
<collectingCountry id="F301F591FF9CFF5CFC748B29E32EFB94" box="[1017,1124,1051,1077]" name="Australia" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Australia</collectingCountry>
: from NE 
<collectingRegion id="49D27BE3FF9CFF5CFB598B29E212FB94" box="[1236,1368,1051,1077]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Queensland</collectingRegion>
along the east, south, and west coasts north to around Dampier, 
<collectingRegion id="49D27BE3FF9CFF5CFC918B72E4ADFBF8" box="[796,999,1087,1114]" country="Australia" name="Western Australia" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Western Australia</collectingRegion>
; from 
<collectingRegion id="49D27BE3FF9CFF5CFBA38B0DE3D1FBF8" box="[1070,1179,1087,1113]" country="New Zealand" name="Auckland" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Auckland</collectingRegion>
Islands, 
<collectingCountry id="F301F591FF9CFF5CFB728B72E2D2FBF8" box="[1279,1432,1087,1114]" name="New Zealand" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, and from several locations in 
<collectingCountry id="F301F591FF9CFF5CFE6C8B51E502FBDC" box="[481,584,1123,1149]" name="Thailand" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. A separate study of this apparently quite diverse group is needed. Therefore only one species from eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F301F591FF9CFF5CFE618BB5E519FB00" box="[492,595,1159,1185]" name="Australia" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Australia</collectingCountry>
is being described here. Collection locations in Australian for material not reported here are shown in 
<figureCitation id="132DA984FF9CFF5CFE448B99E551FB64" box="[457,539,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="85.[151,250,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[365,1227,186,1862]" captionTargetId="figure-15@85.[346,1241,181,1880]" captionTargetPageId="85" captionText="FIGURE 47. Distribution of Glandulotiron and Minitiron (Tironinae, Synopiidae) in Australia. A, Adelaide; B, Brisbane; D, Darwin, Da, Dampier; JB, Jervis Bay; L, Lizard Is.; M, Melbourne; Or.Is., Orpheus Island (type locality of Minitiron); P, Perth; PH, Port Hedland; S, Sydney; SB, Shark Bay; T, Townsville. Dots may represent more than one sample. Open circles: undescribed material of Minitiron." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6572147" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6572147/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
